'''Consolidation''' is a clinical term for solidification into a firm dense mass. It is usually applied to [[induration]] (swelling or hardening of normally soft tissue) of a normally aerated [[lung]] through accumulation of inflammatory cellular exudate in the [[alveoli]] and adjoining ducts. Consolidated tissue is radio-opaque, so that it shows up in [[X-rays]] and [[CT scans|CT (computerized tomography) scans]]. Consolidation is a middle-to-late stage feature in [[pulmonary]] infections.

